        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 1 at 7:21PM MDT by NWS Riverton WY</headline>
        <description>At 721 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Gallatin Lake, which is 12 miles northeast of West Yellowstone,
moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects. Minor hail
damage to vegetation is possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Gallatin Lake around 725 PM MDT.
Grizzly Lake around 735 PM MDT.
Obsidian Cliff around 740 PM MDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

To report severe weather, contact your nearest law enforcement
agency. They will relay your report to the National Weather Service
office in Riverton.</instruction>
